    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2021-07-26</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2021-10-25T14:45:53Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><strong>Stop shielding Assets from Corporate Known Liability by Eliminating non-debtor Releases Act or the SACKLER Act </strong></p> <p>This bill prohibits a bankruptcy court from releasing claims against non-debtors brought by states, tribes, municipalities, or the federal government. However, the bankruptcy court may issue a stay not exceeding 90 days regarding such a claim.</p> <p>Complex bankruptcies may involve creditor claims against non-debtors associated with the debtor, such as the debtor's officers, directors, or employees. Currently, in carrying out a bankruptcy plan, certain courts may release non-debtors from liability (there is a circuit split regarding this practice).</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
